Introduction

This document explains how to install You Don't Know Jack on a WebTV Plus
Internet receiver.

This process is a little complicated. That's because You Don't Know Jack is
not yet deployed on WebTV's service. The final public process will be much
simpler.

What you need:

   * A WebTV Plus Internet receiver. This won't work with a regular WebTV
     Classic Internet receiver. If you are not sure what kind of WebTV you
     have, look on the back. If it has a video in port, it is a WebTV Plus
   * A TV set.
   * A normal phone line. (It's OK if you have to dial '9' first.)
   * About two hours of time. (Fortunately, the box does not have to be
     attended during the download -- you can go and do something else while
     the software downloads.)

Well, it's more complicated that I would like it, but I think if you follow
these directions, you should make it through OK.

What you will do:

  1. Set up your WebTV Plus Internet receiver.
  2. Find out what kind of application ROM it has
  3. Get an Internal 2.1 application ROM:
       1. Connect to the regular WebTV service. (5 minutes)
       2. Log on to the regular service "WebTV Tricks" page. (2 minutes.)
       3. Download an internal 2.1 application ROM. (20 minutes.)
  4. Get an Internal 2.2 application ROM
       1. Connect to the Daily service. (5 minutes)
       2. Log on to the Daily service "WebTV Tricks" page. (2 minutes.)
       3. Download an internal 2.2 application ROM (20 minutes)
  5. Get the game software
       1. Connect to the special Beta WebTV Games service. (5 minutes.)
       2. Subscribe to "You Don't Know Jack" (2 minutes.)
       3. Download the "You Don't Know Jack" software. (60 minutes).

         For WebTV Employees: If your WebTV Plus is already
         connected to the Daily service, you can start at step 4.
         If you already have an internal application ROM, you can
         start at step 5.

Step 1: Setting up your WebTV Plus Internet receiver

Read the manual that came with your WebTV Plus Internet receiver to learn
how to set it up. It's a lot like a VCR -- except that it also has to hook
into the phone line.

Step 2: Identifying the currently installed application ROM

The first step is to identify what kind of application ROM you currently
have installed in your WebTV Plus box. This is easy to do by using the 411
secret code:

  1. Power off the WebTV Box.
  2. Wait for the disk to quiet down. (That is, for the disk head to stop
     seeking.) It is OK for the disk motor to still be spinning.
  3. Type the secret code 411.
  4. If you typed the code correctly, the boxes lights will flash for a
     brief period of time.
  5. If the box lights didn't flash, press the Option key, and then enter
     the secret code again.
  6. Press the Web power button.

You should see a page titled "WebTV Technical Information". Look at the line
that says "Client:"

