Logging on to the WebTV Tricks page

Once you have connected to the WebTV service, the next step is to log onto
the WebTV Tricks page. This is a special page that is used by WebTV and its
business partners.

Do the following to log on to the WebTV Tricks page:

  1. Go to the Web Home page on the service.
  2. Press the GoTo button, which is located in the upper right-hand corner
     of the WebTV keyboard.
  3. A "Address:" dialog box will pop up. If it doesn't, make sure that
     you're on the Web Home page, not the TV Home page.
  4. Type backspace several times, to erase the "http://" that's already
     typed into the box for you.
  5. Type: wtv-tricks:tricks
  6. Press "Return".
  7. You will see a page asking for a password.
       1. In order to access WebTV Tricks you need a password.
       2. The password changes occasionally.
       3. If you are a Bezerk or Jellyvision employee, call Jack Palevich
          (650)614-8441 to get the current password.
       4. Do not give out the password to anyone.
  8. Typing the correct password will take you to a page that has a number
     of links.

Downloading an internal 2.1 application ROM

Now that you are logged on to the WebTV Tricks page, you can download an
internal application ROM. An internal application ROM is required for two
reasons:

  1. It has the ability to launch client-side games, such as You Don't Know
     Jack.
  2. It has the ability to connect to beta servers, such as the Beta Games
     server.

To download an internal application ROM, do the following:

  1. Choose the link "Visit Big Willie's". Hit Enter to go to "Big Willie's
     Flash ROM Download Center".
  2. Choose the link "2.1 Internal, nondebug, app ROM needs boot 2039 (build
     3063)".
  3. Wait about 15 minutes. for the page to download.
  4. You will see an "Updating complete" page.
  5.
     Press the Web Power button to turn off the WebTV Plus.

Step 4: Getting an Internal 2.2 application ROM

 The next step is to use the internal 2.1 application ROM to connect to the
