Connecting to the Daily WebTV service

Once you have downloaded an internal 2.1 application ROM, you can configure
your box to connect to the Daily WebTV service. This is an internal service
that is used to test new software. You need to connect to it in order to
download the games approm. You do this as follows:

  1. Make sure the box is turned off, but still connected to the power.
  2. While the box is turned off, type the following "secret code" on the
     keyboard: 93288
  3. If you did that right, the 3 LEDs will flash briefly. If the LEDs did
     not flash, press the "Option" key, and then try again.
  4. Once you have entered the secret code correctly, turn on the box by
     pressing the "Web Power" button on the keyboard.
  5. Instead of the normal "TV Home" page, you will see a "Connection
     Configuration" page.
       1. The defaults are correct for what we want to do. Don't change any
          of the values.
       2. Select the "Connect" button and press "Return".
  6. Wait for a connection to the Daily WebTV service.

Once you have connected to the Daily service, you will be asked to sign up
for the service again. Type in "auto" for your first name to skip the
sign-up process. You will receive a made-up name and address. You won't be
billed for this second account. By the way, the "auto" short-cut is only
available because you're running an internal application ROM and connected
to an internal service.

Logging on to the WebTV Tricks page

Once you have connected to the Daily WebTV service, the next step is to log
onto the Daily WebTV Tricks page. This is a special page that is used by
WebTV and its business partners.

Do the following to log on to the Daily WebTV Tricks page:

  1. Go to the Web Home page on the service.
  2. Press the GoTo button, which is located in the upper right-hand corner
     of the WebTV keyboard.
  3. A "Address:" dialog box will pop up. If it doesn't, make sure that
     you're on the Web Home page, not the TV Home page.
  4. Type backspace several times, to erase the "http://" that's already
     typed into the box for you.
  5. Type: wtv-tricks:tricks
  6. Press "Return".
  7. You will see a page asking for a password.
       1. In order to access WebTV Tricks you need a password.
       2. The password changes occasionally.
       3. If you are a Bezerk or Jellyvision employee, call Jack Palevich
          (650)614-8441 to get the current password.
       4. Do not give out the password to anyone.
  8. Typing the correct password will take you to a page that has a number
     of links.

Downloading an internal 2.2 application ROM

Now that you are logged on to the Daily Service's WebTV Tricks page, you can
download an internal 2.2 application ROM. An internal 2.2 application ROM is
required for two reasons:

  1. It has the ability to launch client-side games, such as You Don't Know
     Jack.
  2. It has the ability to connect to internal servers, such as the Beta
     Games server.

To download an internal 2.2 application ROM, do the following:

  1. Choose the link "Visit Big Willie's". Hit Enter to go to "Big Willie's
     Flash ROM Download Center".
  2. Choose the pop-up menu "2.2 English (US) Builds..."
  3. Choose the largest, top-most number. It should be 3355 or greater.
  4. Choose the link "nondebug", in the "DAILY" row.
  5. Wait about 15 minutes for the download to complete.
  6. You will see a page titled "Updating complete".
  7. Power off the WebTV box.

Step 5: Getting the Game Software

Now that we have an internal 2.2 application ROM, we can finally download
and play the games. But, we need to connect to yet another service.

Connecting to the Beta WebTV Games service

Once you have downloaded an internal 2.2 application ROM, you can configure
your box to connect to the Beta WebTV Games Service. You do this as follows:

  1. Make sure the box is turned off, but still connected to the power.
  2. While the box is turned off, type the following "secret code" on the
     keyboard: 93288
  3. If you did that right, the 3 LEDs will flash briefly. If the LEDs did
     not flash, press the "Option" key, and then try again.
       1. If it just doesn't seem to work, you may not have an internal ROM.
          Try downloading an internal ROM again.
  4. Once you have entered the secret code correctly, turn on the box by
     pressing the "Web Power" button on the keyboard.
  5. Instead of the normal "TV Home" page, you will see a "Connection Setup"
     page.
       1. Choose the radio button "Custom:".
       2. Enter the Address: 172.17.64.127
       3. Enter the port address 24315
       4. Select the "Connect" button and press "Return".
  6. Wait for a connection to the Beta WebTV Games service.
       1. If you can't get connected, call Jack to make sure that the Beta
          Games service is running OK.

Once you have connected to the Beta WebTV Games service, you will be asked
to sign up for the service again. Type in "auto" for your first name to skip
the sign-up process. You will receive a made-up name and address. You won't
be billed for this third account. By the way, the "auto" short-cut is only
available because you're connected to an internal service.

Once the sign-up process is complete you will be sent to the Web Home Page
of the Beta WebTV Games service.

In the future, each time you connect to the web you will be connected to the
Beta WebTV Games service.

Subscribing to You Don't Know Jack

Once you are connected to the Web Home Page of the Beta WebTV Games service,
you can subscribe to You Don't Know Jack.

To subscribe, follow these steps:

  1. Click on the "Using WebTV" link that's located on the left-hand-side of
     the home page.
  2. Click on the "Customize WebTV" link that's located 1/2 way down the
     right-hand side of the Setup page.
  3. Click on the "Games" link located half way down the right-hand column.
       1. If you don't see a Games link, you are not connected to the Beta
          Games WebTV Service. Go to the "Connecting to the Beta Games WebTV
          Service" section.
  4. Click on the "Enable Games" radio button.
  5. Click on "Continue"
  6. Enable the "You Don't Know Jack" checkbox.
  7. If you want, you can click on the other game checkboxes too. You can
     also return to this page later to add or remove games.
  8. Click on "Continue"
  9. Make sure that "Auto update" is enabled. (It should be, by default.)
 10. Click on "Continue".
 11. Retrieving Files. Wait about an hour to download the game software.

It takes quite a while to download You Don't Know Jack. The exact time
depends upon which software is already on your box. If you already have all
the software on your box, it will take as little as 20 seconds to verify
that everything's OK. If you have nothing on your box yet, it might take as
much as an hour and a half.

Once the software has been downloaded, you will see a status page that
explains whether the process succeeded or failed.

   * If you failed, press the "Home" key to return to the Web Home Page and
     try subscribing to "You Don't Know Jack" again.
   * If you succeeded, press Continue to go to the games page.
   * Once you are on the games page, power off the WebTV Plus Box.

