Playing You Don'tĀ Know Jack

Once you've subscribed to games and downloaded the You Don't Know Jack
software, a Games link will appear on the TV Home Page.Ā The Games link is
located to the left of the TV window. If you don't see a Games link, go to
the section "Subscribing to You Don't Know Jack".

Select the Games link and press return to go to the Games page.

The Games page shows which games you have installed. There should be a "You
Don't Know Jack" link. Select it and press Return to start "You Don't Know
Jack". The screen will go blank for about 20 seconds, and then it will go
white as "You Don't Know Jack" begins.

Quitting You Don't Know Jack

Press the Esc key, and then the Q key, to quit playing "You Don't Know
Jack". This will return you (after 20 seconds) to the TV Home Page.

Turning off the WebTV Plus box

Use the Power key (from the Web world or the TV Home Page)Ā to turn off the
WebTV Plus box. While playing a game, Power will return you to the TV Home
Page.

Playing You Don't Know Jack again

Once you've configured the box and played You Don't Know Jack once, the box
should stay configured. Use the "Games" link off the TV Home Page to start
playing "You Don't Know Jack".

Troubleshooting

   * If the box stops responding, wait a minute to see if it reboots by
     itself. It has a hardware watchdog timer, so it should always restart.
   * Once it restarts, wait 30 seconds, until the disk stops spinning. Then
     press the Web Power button.
   * If you get lost, contact Jack Palevich by phone or e-mail.

Reporting bugs

Report bugs by sending e-mail to palevich@corp.webtv.net. In addition, the
box has the ability to semi-automatically log crashes.

In order to automatically log a game crash, you must connect the the WebTV
Web Home Page. Do this after the crash, but before you play another game.
All you have to do is use the "Web Home" link from the TV Home Page, and log
onto the service. Once you do that, you can return to the TV Home page and
play some more games. The crash log is uploaded automatically when you
connect to the service.

Nightly Downloads

If you leave the WebTV Box plugged in and connected to the phone line, and
you have TV listing downloads enabled, your box will automatically call back
to WebTV each night to see if there are any updates. However, currently this
only works if you have TV Listings enabled. To check if you have TV listings
enabled:

  1. Go to the TV Home Page.
  2. Click on Settings.
  3. Click on Listings setup.
  4. Follow the instructions.
  5. Make sure that Auto retrieve is checked.

If for some reason you can't leave the WebTV Plus box connected to the phone
line, you can manually trigger a nightly download by doing the following:

   * Make sure the box is connected to a phone line.
   * Power off the box.
   * Wait 30 seconds for the disk to stop spinning.
   * Type in the secret code 1111.
   * The box will automatically power on, go through a nightly download
     cycle, and then power off again.

