Returning to the Production or Daily Service

You Don't Know Jack testers should stay with the Beta games service. Other
users will probably want to return to either the Regular or the Daily
service. Once you have installed an offline game, you should be able to play
it no matter which service you are connected to. The only requirement is
that you must continue to use some flavor of Client 2.2 approm.

To return to the Production service

  1. Make sure the box is turned off, but still connected to the power.
  2. While the box is turned off, type the following "secret code" on the
     keyboard: 93288
  3. If you did that right, the 3 LEDs will flash briefly. If the LEDs did
     not flash, press the "Option" key, and then try again.
  4. Once you have entered the secret code correctly, turn on the box by
     pressing the "Web Power" button on the keyboard.
  5. Instead of the normal "TV Home" page, you will see a "Connection
     Configuration" page.
       1. Select on the combo-popup menu that says "Daily".
       2. Press Return.
       3. Select the "Production" item.
       4. Press Return.
       5. Select the "Connect" button and press "Return".
  6. Wait for a connection to the Production WebTV service.

To return to the Daily service

  1. Make sure the box is turned off, but still connected to the power.
  2. While the box is turned off, type the following "secret code" on the
     keyboard: 93288
  3. If you did that right, the 3 LEDs will flash briefly. If the LEDs did
     not flash, press the "Option" key, and then try again.
  4. Once you have entered the secret code correctly, turn on the box by
     pressing the "Web Power" button on the keyboard.
  5. Instead of the normal "TV Home" page, you will see a "Connection
     Configuration" page.
       1. You don't have to select a service, since the default is to
          connect to Daily.
       2. Select the "Connect" button and press "Return".
  6. Wait for a connection to the Daily WebTV service.

